{
  "stem": "26888.6",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I-- I also made food for some of them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So that's how I was better in a little bit.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "To bring up the children, it was a very, very-- we had a very hard time with-- you know, that's why we had two, and we didn't have more, because-- later on, my husband got a better job.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon me?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I have six grandchildren, I have one great-grandchild.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Jonathan, Daniel, Stephanie-- that's my daughter, my son is Shannon, Ariel, and Jamie-- that's my daughter in Canada.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I have now a great-grandchild, Yael Devorah.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My granddaughter.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I told you, she is Stephanie.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And her husband, [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Joshua. ?]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] It didn't change.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I kept kosher, right away.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Matter of fact, when I came home, I was looking for kosher.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my friends tell me, are you crazy?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You came home from such a terrible place, and now you're looking for kosher?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I says, yes, I'm looking for kosher, because I'm brought up like that, and I'm not going to change it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My family-- I don't want to be different.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And of course I'm not maybe Hasidic-- because my family was-- but we don't do nothing.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We keep strictly kosher.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And my husband is always in Shul, and I am in Shul.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we keep a nice Jewish family [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I just couldn't throw away my religion.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Sometimes you-- you know, sometimes you think about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "How does-- you know, rebel a little bit.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Still how God could do that, think like that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Such a religious people, such a fine people, such-- you know, life goes on.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the message is that I-- if we would know before what was happening to us, maybe we would have done it different.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
